      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "But the sea was for the priests to wash in.—The Hebrew words have been transposed apparently. The same infinitive (lĕrohçāh) occurs in Exodus 30:18; Exodus 40:30, in a similar context. Instead of all this, the Syriac and Arabic versions read: “put them five on the right hand and five on the left, that the priests might wash in them their hands and their feet,” which appears to be derived from Exodus 30:19; Exodus 40:31.",
